  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6767.78 sitting right in the thick negative gamma zone between 6750-6760 (-56B to -53B), dealers are actively buying this dip as they're short gamma and need to hedge dynamically. The regime flip into BREAKOUT mode with -13.2B total GEX means dealers will amplify moves - they'll continue buying weakness toward 6750 and aggressively sell any rally back toward the 6800 positive gamma wall (+51B). Watch 6750 as the critical amplifying floor where dealer buying should intensify, while 6800 becomes the hard resistance ceiling where dealer selling kicks in.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect volatile swings between 6750 and 6800 with dealers pushing price around rather than stabilizing it.",
